    "Background": {
      "text": "Primary bacterial infection of skeletal muscle\nAlso known as myositis tropicans, more common in tropical settings\nTemperate climates in immune compromised patients\nMainly disease of children, age 2-5 most common",
      "subsections": {
        "Pathophysiology": {
          "text": "Transient bacteremia after blunt trauma to muscle group, or vigorous exercise\n[1]\nMost commonly\nStaph aureus\n, followed by\nStrep\npyogenes,\npneumococcus\n, neisseria,\nhaemophilus\n, yersinia,\npseudomonas\n,\nklebsiella\n, and\nE. coli",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Risk_Factors": {
          "text": "DM\nHIV\nIVDU\nRenal failure\nImmunosuppression",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
